Entity Relationship Diagarm (ERD)

Entity
Represents a person,place or thin that you want to track in a database.
This will become a table in the database.
Each occurence of the entity is an "entity instance" => "row in the table

e.g. 
 Student Entity : A table in DB => Is more of a Container which holds many different students. All of the things like a student will be gorup together udner Student.
 

Attribute
Describe various characteristics about an individual entity


Primary Key/Identifier
An attribute or group of attributes that **uniquely** identifies an instance of the entity.



Relationship
Descirbes how on e or more entities interact with each other.
A **verb** is often used to descvibe the relationship.





Cardinality
The count of instances that are allowed or are necessary between entity relationships.
Minimum/Maximum


